Class JsonHttpClient, HttpResponse executeUnparsed(HttpMethod, GenericUrl, Object)

Builds and executes a HttpRequest. Subclasses may override if specific behavior is required, for example if a sequence of requests need to be built instead instead of a single request.

Callers are responsible for closing the response's content input stream by calling HttpResponse.ignore.

@param method HTTP Method type @param url The complete URL of the service where requests should be sent @param body A POJO that can be serialized into JSON or {@code null} for none @return HttpRequest type @throws IOException if the request fails @since 1.7
